---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import OpenSource from '../components/OpenSource.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <main class="hero">
    <div class="marker">
      <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M12 19h8"/><path d="m4 17 6-6-6-6"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h1 class="title">Hi, I'm Martin</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer with over a decade of
        experience building applications for the web.
      </p>
      <p>
        I wrote my first line of code in 2010. I've since taken dozens of
        web apps from conception to production, becoming fluent in a broad range
        of web technologies along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've shipped a lot of Ruby, Rails, Javascript, Typescript, and C++. More
        recently, I've been building with WebAssembly, focusing on how it expands
        the browser's capabilities. I've been especially interested in
        <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://drs.software/blog/understanding-webassembly---the-fundamentals/">
        porting applications to the browser using WebAssembly.</a>
        I’m constantly tinkering with new (to me) tech.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’m currently the Lead Software Engineer at
        <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://drs.software/">DRS Software,</a>
        where we build advanced web applications and support organisations in
        modernising their existing software using Wasm.
      </p>
    </div>

    <OpenSource />
  </main>
</Layout>
